# Android Security Testing

> Mobile application penetration testing methodology for Android apps.

---

## 🛠️ Setup

```bash
# Required tools
- jadx (decompiler)
- apktool (decompile/recompile)
- adb (Android Debug Bridge)
- frida (dynamic instrumentation)
- objection (frida-based mobile testing)
- Burp Suite (traffic interception)
- MobSF (automated analysis)
- drozer (attack framework)
```

---

## 📦 APK Analysis (Static)

```bash
# Decompile APK with jadx (best for Java code)
jadx -d output_dir target.apk

# Decompile with apktool (smali code + resources)
apktool d target.apk -o output_dir

# Recompile after modification
apktool b output_dir -o modified.apk

# Sign modified APK
keytool -genkey -v -keystore my.keystore -alias alias_name -keyalg RSA -keysize 2048 -validity 10000
jarsigner -verbose -sigalg SHA1withRSA -digestalg SHA1 -keystore my.keystore modified.apk alias_name
zipalign -v 4 modified.apk final.apk

# Extract APK (it's a zip)
unzip target.apk -d extracted/
```

