## 🔓 SSL Pinning Bypass

```bash
# Using objection
objection --gadget com.target.app explore
# Then in objection shell:
android sslpinning disable

# Using Frida script
frida -U -f com.target.app --no-pause -l ssl_bypass.js

# Common SSL bypass scripts:
# - https://github.com/WoWoX/frida-multiple-unpinning
# - https://github.com/httptoolkit/frida-android-unpinning

# Using apktool (manual)
# Find and modify certificate pinning code in smali
# Or add network_security_config.xml

# network_security_config.xml (for older bypasses)
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<network-security-config>
  <base-config>
    <trust-anchors>
      <certificates src="system" />
      <certificates src="user" />
    </trust-anchors>
  </base-config>
</network-security-config>
```

