## 🕵️ Traffic Interception (Burp Suite)

```bash
# Setup proxy on device
# Settings -> WiFi -> Proxy -> Manual
# Host: 192.168.x.x (your IP)
# Port: 8080

# Install Burp CA certificate
# Download from http://burp
# Install on device (Settings -> Security -> Install certificate)

# For Android 7+ (user certs not trusted by default)
# Option 1: Root device + move cert to system store
adb shell su -c "mount -o rw,remount /system"
adb push burp.cer /system/etc/security/cacerts/
adb shell chmod 644 /system/etc/security/cacerts/burp.cer

# Option 2: Patch manifest (add network_security_config)
# Option 3: Use Frida to bypass SSL pinning
```

