## 📋 Android Pentesting Checklist

- [ ] Static analysis with jadx/MobSF
- [ ] Check AndroidManifest.xml for misconfigurations
- [ ] Find hardcoded secrets/API keys
- [ ] Test exported components
- [ ] Intercept traffic with Burp Suite
- [ ] Bypass SSL pinning
- [ ] Check local storage (SharedPrefs, SQLite, files)
- [ ] Test WebView for XSS/JS injection
- [ ] Check deep links for parameter injection
- [ ] Test backup functionality
- [ ] Check for sensitive data in logcat
- [ ] Test intent-based attacks with drozer
- [ ] Check for root detection and bypass

---

## 🧠 Tips

- **MobSF** automates most static analysis — run it first
- **objection** is Frida without writing scripts — very fast
- Always check **logcat** during app usage — devs often leave debug logs
- **Exported activities** can be launched without authentication
- **Deep links** (custom schemas) often have injection vulnerabilities
- Check `.well-known/assetlinks.json` for domain validation issues

